universum.studios.android.fragment.annotation.handler

Interface ActionBarFragmentAnnotationHandler

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AnnotationHandler, FragmentAnnotationHandler
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    WebFragmentAnnotationHandler

    public interface ActionBarFragmentAnnotationHandler
extends FragmentAnnotationHandler
    A FragmentAnnotationHandler extended interface for annotation handlers from the Fragments library that are used to handle processing of annotations attached to classes derived from the ActionBar Fragment classes provided by this library.
    Author:
    Martin Albedinsky
    See Also:
    ActionBarFragment

      • configureActionBar

        void configureActionBar(@NonNull
                        ActionBarDelegate actionBarDelegate)
        Performs configuration of the ActionBar wrapped by the given actionBarDelegate based on @ActionBarOptions annotation (if presented).
        Parameters:
        actionBarDelegate - The delegate with ActionBar to configure.

      • hasOptionsMenu

        boolean hasOptionsMenu()
        Returns a boolean flag indicating whether there is @MenuOptions annotation presented or @ActionBarOptions annotation with home as up indicator enabled.
        Returns:
        True if the related fragment should indicate that it wants to participate on population of the options menu via Fragment.setHasOptionsMenu(boolean), false otherwise.

      • shouldClearOptionsMenu

        boolean shouldClearOptionsMenu()
        Returns a boolean flag obtained from @MenuOptions annotation (if presented) from MenuOptions.clear() attribute.
        Returns:
        True to clear menu in context of the related fragment before it is populated with menu items of that fragment, false otherwise.

      • getOptionsMenuResource

        @MenuRes
int getOptionsMenuResource(@MenuRes
                                     int defaultResource)
        Returns the menu resource obtained from @MenuOptions annotation (if presented) from MenuOptions.value() attribute.
        Parameters:
        defaultResource - Default menu resource to be returned if there is no annotation presented or resource is not specified.
        Returns:
        Via annotation specified menu resource or defaultResource.

      • getOptionsMenuFlags

        int getOptionsMenuFlags(int defaultFlags)
        Returns the menu flags obtained from @MenuOptions annotation (if presented) from MenuOptions.flags() attribute.
        Parameters:
        defaultFlags - Default menu flags to be returned if there is no annotation presented.
        Returns:
        Via annotation specified menu flags or defaultFlags.

      • handleCreateActionMode

        boolean handleCreateActionMode(@NonNull
                               ActionMode actionMode,
                               @NonNull
                               Menu menu)
        Handles creation of the specified actionMode by inflating its menu with options specified via @ActionModeOptions annotation.
        Parameters:
        actionMode - The started action mode of which creation to handle.
        menu - The menu where to possibly inflate menu options.
        Returns:
        True if there were inflated some menu options into the specified menu, false otherwise.
